
    Gunmen abduct Italian aid worker in Kenya

        

    
        
                
                
            
        A group of unidentified gunmen have abducted an Italian woman working for an aid organisation in south-east Kenya, police say.The men, reportedly armed with rifles, "fired indiscriminately" before taking the 23-year-old volunteer from an area in Kilifi County.A number of people were also reportedly wounded and were taken to hospital.The reason for the attack and the identity of the attackers has not yet been established, police said. 
            

